data.content:
Three breaking changes hit your code. Here's each one and the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ŌĆö now takes `Func<>`, not `Expression<Func<>>`

Your manual expression tree building **won't compile** anymore. Replace it with the much simpler non-expression lambda:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

No more `Expression.Lambda`, `Expression.Call`, etc. ŌĆö conditionals go directly inside the lambda body.

---

### 2. Complex type column names ŌĆö now auto-uniquified & nested paths changed

Two sub-changes:

- **Same-named properties** across complex types (e.g. `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street`) previously shared one column silently. Now EF appends a number (`Street`, `Street1`). To keep the old shared column:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});
```

- **Nested complex types** now use the full path. `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was column `BillingAddress_City`, now becomes `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. To preserve old names:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

**If you have existing migrations**, run `dotnet ef migrations add UpgradeEfCore10` after upgrading ŌĆö inspect the generated migration carefully for any unintended column renames, and pin names with `HasColumnName` where the old names must be preserved.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ŌĆö new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (for redacted SQL logging). Add it to your implementation:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ŌåÉ new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (sensitive data redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual execution SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
